		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName> <date>May 30<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1864</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Rev Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">The United Heb cong<lb/> of this city&#44; having a Petition as candidate<lb/> for Rabbi &#38; Preacher of our cong. from the <persName>Rev<lb/> Dr Henry Vidaver</persName>&#44; formerly Rabbi &#38; Preacher<lb/> of the cong Rodolf <add>Rodelph</add> Sholom of your city&#44;<lb/> refers among others Testimonials to yourself<lb/> as regards his qualifications &#38; character<lb/> though he may differ with you in some Theolo&#95;<lb/>gical Points&#44; the cong here therefore beg of you<lb/> that you may give us at your earliest con&#95;<lb/><sic>vinience</sic>&#44; your opinions as to the abilities&#44; qualifi&#95;<lb/>cations and character of <persName>Dr Vidaver</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Your most obedient</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Henry Auerbach</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Sec.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p><sic>Adress</sic> <persName role="author">Henry Auerbach</persName></p>
				<p>care of <persName>Wm. Keiler</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>MO</placeName></p>
				<p rend="Note&#58;">&#35;73 written in pencil and circled at top left corner of the page.</p>
